verses.text_plain: And Joshua the son of Nun sent out of Shittim two men to spy secretly, saying, Go view the land, even Jericho. And they went, and came into an harlot’s house, named Rahab, and lodged there.
verses.verse_html:
1And Joshua the son of Nun sent out of Shittim two men to spy secretly, saying, Go view the land, even Jericho. And they went, and came into an harlot’s house, named Rahab, and lodged there. ▼
▼ sent: or, had sent
 , ▼
▼ lodged: Heb. lay

footnotes.body_html: ▼ sent: or, had sent

verses.text_plain: And it was told the king of Jericho, saying, Behold, there came men in hither to night of the children of Israel to search out the country.
verses.verse_html: 2And it was told the king of Jericho, saying, Behold, there came men in hither to night of the children of Israel to search out the country.

verses.text_plain: And the king of Jericho sent unto Rahab, saying, Bring forth the men that are come to thee, which are entered into thine house: for they be come to search out all the country.
verses.verse_html: 3And the king of Jericho sent unto Rahab, saying, Bring forth the men that are come to thee, which are entered into thine house: for they be come to search out all the country.

verses.text_plain: And the woman took the two men, and hid them, and said thus, There came men unto me, but I wist not whence they were:
verses.verse_html: 4And the woman took the two men, and hid them, and said thus, There came men unto me, but I wist not whence they were:

verses.text_plain: And it came to pass about the time of shutting of the gate, when it was dark, that the men went out: whither the men went I wot not: pursue after them quickly; for ye shall overtake them.
verses.verse_html: 5And it came to pass about the time of shutting of the gate, when it was dark, that the men went out: whither the men went I wot not: pursue after them quickly; for ye shall overtake them.

verses.text_plain: But she had brought them up to the roof of the house, and hid them with the stalks of flax, which she had laid in order upon the roof.
verses.verse_html: 6But she had brought them up to the roof of the house, and hid them with the stalks of flax, which she had laid in order upon the roof.

tokens.text: But she had brought them up
which she had laid in order

verses.text_plain: And the men pursued after them the way to Jordan unto the fords: and as soon as they which pursued after them were gone out, they shut the gate.
verses.verse_html: 7And the men pursued after them the way to Jordan unto the fords: and as soon as they which pursued after them were gone out, they shut the gate.

tokens.text: and as soon as they which pursued

verses.text_plain: And before they were laid down, she came up unto them upon the roof;
verses.verse_html: 8And before they were laid down, she came up unto them upon the roof;

tokens.text: And before they were laid down

verses.text_plain: And she said unto the men, I know that the Lord hath given you the land, and that your terror is fallen upon us, and that all the inhabitants of the land faint because of you.
verses.verse_html:
9And she said unto the men, I know that the Lord hath given you the land, and that your terror is fallen upon us, and that all the inhabitants of the land faint because of you. ▼
▼ faint: Heb. melt

tokens.text: upon us, and that all the inhabitants

verses.text_plain: For we have heard how the Lord dried up the water of the Red sea for you, when ye came out of Egypt; and what ye did unto the two kings of the Amorites, that were on the other side Jordan, Sihon and Og, whom ye utterly destroyed.
verses.verse_html: 10For we have heard how the Lord dried up the water of the Red sea for you, when ye came out of Egypt; and what ye did unto the two kings of the Amorites, that were on the other side Jordan, Sihon and Og, whom ye utterly destroyed.

verses.text_plain: And as soon as we had heard these things, our hearts did melt, neither did there remain any more courage in any man, because of you: for the Lord your God, he is God in heaven above, and in earth beneath.
verses.verse_html:
11And as soon as we had heard these things, our hearts did melt, neither did there remain any more courage in any man, because of you: for the Lord your God, he is God in heaven above, and in earth beneath. ▼
▼ did there…: Heb. rose up

verses.text_plain: Now therefore, I pray you, swear unto me by the Lord, since I have shewed you kindness, that ye will also shew kindness unto my father’s house, and give me a true token:
verses.verse_html: 12Now therefore, I pray you, swear unto me by the Lord, since I have shewed you kindness, that ye will also shew kindness unto my father’s house, and give me a true token:

tokens.text: Now therefore, I pray you, swear

verses.text_plain: And that ye will save alive my father, and my mother, and my brethren, and my sisters, and all that they have, and deliver our lives from death.
verses.verse_html: 13And that ye will save alive my father, and my mother, and my brethren, and my sisters, and all that they have, and deliver our lives from death.

tokens.text: and all that they have, and deliver

verses.text_plain: And the men answered her, Our life for yours, if ye utter not this our business. And it shall be, when the Lord hath given us the land, that we will deal kindly and truly with thee.
verses.verse_html:
14And the men answered her, Our life for yours, if ye utter not this our business. And it shall be, when the Lord hath given us the land, that we will deal kindly and truly with thee. ▼
▼ for…: Heb. instead of you to die

verses.text_plain: Then she let them down by a cord through the window: for her house was upon the town wall, and she dwelt upon the wall.
verses.verse_html: 15Then she let them down by a cord through the window: for her house was upon the town wall, and she dwelt upon the wall.

verses.text_plain: And she said unto them, Get you to the mountain, lest the pursuers meet you; and hide yourselves there three days, until the pursuers be returned: and afterward may ye go your way.
verses.verse_html: 16And she said unto them, Get you to the mountain, lest the pursuers meet you; and hide yourselves there three days, until the pursuers be returned: and afterward may ye go your way.

verses.text_plain: And the men said unto her, We will be blameless of this thine oath which thou hast made us swear.
verses.verse_html: 17And the men said unto her, We will be blameless of this thine oath which thou hast made us swear.

tokens.text: which thou hast made us swear

verses.text_plain: Behold, when we come into the land, thou shalt bind this line of scarlet thread in the window which thou didst let us down by: and thou shalt bring thy father, and thy mother, and thy brethren, and all thy father’s household, home unto thee.
verses.verse_html:
18Behold, when we come into the land, thou shalt bind this line of scarlet thread in the window which thou didst let us down by: and thou shalt bring thy father, and thy mother, and thy brethren, and all thy father’s household, home unto thee. ▼
▼ bring: Heb. gather

tokens.text: which thou didst let us down by

verses.text_plain: And it shall be, that whosoever shall go out of the doors of thy house into the street, his blood shall be upon his head, and we will be guiltless: and whosoever shall be with thee in the house, his blood shall be on our head, if any hand be upon him.
verses.verse_html: 19And it shall be, that whosoever shall go out of the doors of thy house into the street, his blood shall be upon his head, and we will be guiltless: and whosoever shall be with thee in the house, his blood shall be on our head, if any hand be upon him.

tokens.text: and whosoever shall be with thee in the house

verses.text_plain: And if thou utter this our business, then we will be quit of thine oath which thou hast made us to swear.
verses.verse_html: 20And if thou utter this our business, then we will be quit of thine oath which thou hast made us to swear.

tokens.text: which thou hast made us to swear

verses.text_plain: And she said, According unto your words, so be it. And she sent them away, and they departed: and she bound the scarlet line in the window.
verses.verse_html: 21And she said, According unto your words, so be it. And she sent them away, and they departed: and she bound the scarlet line in the window.

tokens.text: it. And she sent them away

verses.text_plain: And they went, and came unto the mountain, and abode there three days, until the pursuers were returned: and the pursuers sought them throughout all the way, but found them not.
verses.verse_html: 22And they went, and came unto the mountain, and abode there three days, until the pursuers were returned: and the pursuers sought them throughout all the way, but found them not.

verses.text_plain: So the two men returned, and descended from the mountain, and passed over, and came to Joshua the son of Nun, and told him all things that befell them:
verses.verse_html: 23So the two men returned, and descended from the mountain, and passed over, and came to Joshua the son of Nun, and told him all things that befell them:

verses.text_plain: And they said unto Joshua, Truly the Lord hath delivered into our hands all the land; for even all the inhabitants of the country do faint because of us.
verses.verse_html:
24And they said unto Joshua, Truly the Lord hath delivered into our hands all the land; for even all the inhabitants of the country do faint because of us. ▼
